               <p>ROBERT SURMAN. I am footman to Sir 
               <persName id="t18160710-80-person591">
                  James 
                  Graham
               <interp inst="t18160710-80-person591" type="surname" value="Graham"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160710-80-person591" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160710-80-person591" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; he lives at <placeName id="t18160710-80-crimeloc422">No. 1, Portland-place</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18160710-80-crimeloc422" type="placeName" value="No. 1, Portland-place"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18160710-80-crimeloc422" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160710-80-off419 t18160710-80-crimeloc422"></join>. I lost this coat on the 4th of July; I got up in the morning of that day, and cleaned my stibes and knives, and unlocked the area gate; I then went for some knives. I had left the over night; and while I was gone, the prisoner came in, and took the great coat in question off a peg in the servant's hall; he went out, and I followed him, in consequence of information, and seized him; I brought him back with the coat, and sent for an officer.</p>

               <p>
